# Tooling Priority

Before reaching for PowerShell, Python, or other manual workarounds:

- Check available MCP tools first and use them when they fit the task.
- Check available skills and follow a relevant one instead of improvising.
- Prefer Cursor built-in tools over shell/script equivalents, e.g.:
  - Read instead of cat/Get-Content
  - Glob/Grep instead of find/dir/Select-String
  - StrReplace/Write instead of sed/awk/echo redirection
  - WebFetch/WebSearch instead of curl/Invoke-WebRequest
- Only fall back to PowerShell/Python/CLI when no MCP tool, skill, or built-in tool covers the task, or when they were blocked.
- If you do fall back, say briefly why the preferred tool was not used.
